# Matex B2B Marketplace — Core Architecture

## Project Identity
Matex is a **Canadian B2B recycled materials marketplace** built on a **MCP-First architecture**.
Stack: pnpm monorepo · TypeScript 5.4 · Next.js 14 (App Router) · Supabase (PostgreSQL 15 + PostGIS) · Redis (Upstash) · Stripe Connect.
> "Every module is an MCP server. Every integration is a bridge. Every interaction is a tool call."

## Four Architecture Layers
| Layer | Responsibility | Components |
|---|---|---|
| **L1 Clients** | User-facing interfaces | Next.js web, React Native mobile, AI Agents, 3rd-party ERP |
| **L2 MCP Gateway** | Routing, auth, rate limiting, load balancing | JWT middleware, request router |
| **L3 MCP Servers** | All business logic | 21 local servers + 13 external bridges |
| **L4 Infrastructure** | Shared services | PostgreSQL (Supabase), Redis, Event Bus, S3 Storage, log store |

## Monorepo Layout
```
apps/web                        — Next.js 14 frontend
apps/mcp-gateway                — MCP Gateway (routes all tool calls)
packages/mcp-servers/*-mcp      — One MCP server per domain
packages/bridges/*-bridge       — External service adapters
packages/shared/types           — @matex/types
packages/shared/utils           — @matex/utils
infrastructure/supabase/        — DB migrations and seed data
docs/database/                  — Canonical schema reference
```

