## Event Bus Architecture
- Implemented via **Redis Streams** (ordered, ACK-based, consumer groups per server)
- **Supabase Realtime** for client-facing live events (auctions, chat)
- Event naming: `{server}.{entity}.{action}` — e.g., `bidding.bid.placed`, `escrow.funds.released`
- Retention: 7 days hot (Redis), then archived to S3
- Any server can replay from a stream offset for recovery
- `log-mcp` subscribes to ALL events on the bus — mandatory

## Request Flow (Every Tool Call)
1. Client → MCP Gateway (JWT validated, rate limit checked)
2. Gateway → target MCP server
3. MCP server executes, calls other servers or bridges as needed
4. MCP server publishes events to Event Bus
5. `log-mcp` captures the full request/response cycle
6. Event subscribers (notifications, analytics, etc.) react asynchronously

## Primary Key & Data Type Standards
| Concern | Type |
|---|---|
| All PKs | `UUID` via `uuid_generate_v4()` — never `SERIAL` |
| All monetary amounts | `DECIMAL(12,2)` in **CAD** unless schema states otherwise |
| All timestamps | `TIMESTAMPTZ` (never bare `TIMESTAMP`) |
| All geography | `GEOGRAPHY(Point, 4326)` via PostGIS |
| Flexible structured data | `JSONB` |
| Status/type fields | Named PostgreSQL `ENUM` — never bare `VARCHAR` |

## Client Types
1. **Web App (Next.js)** — SSR, MCP SDK client, Supabase Realtime for live auctions/chat
2. **Mobile App (React Native + Expo)** — offline-first (WatermelonDB), camera-first workflows, biometric auth
3. **AI Agents** — direct MCP Gateway access with delegated auth
4. **Third-Party Integrators** — ERP/accounting via MCP or REST adapter

## Availability & Performance Targets
| Metric | Target |
|---|---|
| Platform uptime | 99.9% |
| API response (p95) | < 200ms read, < 500ms write |
| Auction bid processing | < 200ms end-to-end |
| Event bus delivery | < 500ms |
| Log write latency | < 50ms (async) |
